  "text": "The HT115(DE3) E. coli bacteria producing dsRNA against cdc-25.1 (Andy Golden NIDDK/NIH, Bethesda MD, USA), skn-1 (T. Keith Blackwell, Harvard Medical School, Boston MA, USA), wdr-23 (Keith P. Choe, University of Florida, Gainesville FL, USA), vhp-1 and tir-1 (Source BioScience Geneservice, Cambridge, United Kingdom) were used in our study. RNAi feeding E. coli clones were grown overnight in LB medium containing 100 mg/ml ampicillin. RNAi treatment was performed as described by Shapira et al. [CITATION_1] . Worms were grown on RNAi bacteria from hatching till young adult stage. If several RNAi constructs were used in one condition, ON cultures of the feeding bacteria strains were mixed equally. Empty vector containing HT115(DE3) bacteria (EV) was used as a control in all cases.",
